Spawning Other Applications

    This example shows how to use the DOS/4G API to load and run a DOS/4G
    application from another DOS/4G application.  The example shows the
    two different ways a spawned program can be executed using the API.
    The spawned program is first run using D32RunReturn, so control is
    returned to the spawner when the spawned program exits.  The program
    is then run again, using D32Run, and when the spawned program exits,
    the spawning program will terminate also.
 	
    The example consists of the following files, in the EXAMPLES\4GRUN
    directory:

    4GRUN.C     32-bit code source for spawning program.
    
    4GRUN2.C    32-bit code source for spawned program.
    
    MAKEFILE    Polymake-configured makefile to build all the example
                executables using either Microsoft VC 4.x and/or 
                Watcom v10.5.
